# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TIME-BUCKET SPLIT DEFINITIONS
#
# All models use the same holdout and CV structure.
# time_bucket ranges from 1–20 (each bucket = 30 seconds).
# Bucket 0 is always dropped (pre-auction / incomplete).
#
# HOLDOUT SPLIT (80/20 on bucket order):
#   train : time_bucket in [1, 2, ..., 16]   (buckets 1–16)
#   test  : time_bucket in [17, 18, 19, 20]  (buckets 17–20)
#
# 5-FOLD TimeSeriesSplit (applied within training buckets 1–16):
#   Fold 1 : train=4–6    val=7–8
#   Fold 2 : train=4–8    val=9–10
#   Fold 3 : train=4–10   val=11–12
#   Fold 4 : train=4–12   val=13–14
#   Fold 5 : train=4–14   val=15–16
#
# NOTE: TimeSeriesSplit always trains on strictly earlier buckets
# than it validates on — no look-ahead leakage.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ALL_BUCKETS        = list(range(1, 21))       # buckets 1–20
TRAIN_BUCKETS      = list(range(1, 17))       # 1–16  (holdout train)
TEST_BUCKETS       = list(range(17, 21))      # 17–20 (holdout test)
